{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":764,"text":"Let's go south."},{"time":4094,"text":"All of you are actually going south."},{"time":10539,"text":"This is the direction of south, this way,"},{"time":15229,"text":"and if you go 8,000 kilometers\nout of the back of this room,"},{"time":21749,"text":"you will come to as far south\nas you can go anywhere on Earth,"},{"time":26982,"text":"the Pole itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29393,"text":"Now, I am not an explorer."},{"time":33201,"text":"I'm not an environmentalist."},{"time":36753,"text":"I'm actually just a survivor,"},{"time":40282,"text":"and these photographs\nthat I'm showing you here are dangerous."},{"time":45851,"text":"They are the ice melt\nof the South and North Poles."},{"time":51976,"text":"And ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":53516,"text":"we need to listen to what\nthese places are telling us,"},{"time":59944,"text":"and if we don't, we will end up\nwith our own survival situation"},{"time":66190,"text":"here on planet Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69636,"text":"I have faced head-on these places,"},{"time":75668,"text":"and to walk across a melting ocean of ice"},{"time":80196,"text":"is without doubt\nthe most frightening thing"},{"time":83330,"text":"that's ever happened to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87117,"text":"Antarctica is such a hopeful place."},{"time":93064,"text":"It is protected by \nthe Antarctic Treaty, signed in 1959."},{"time":100845,"text":"In 1991, a 50-year agreement\nwas entered into"},{"time":107100,"text":"that stops any exploitation in Antarctica,"},{"time":112855,"text":"and this agreement could be altered,"},{"time":117695,"text":"changed, modified, or even abandoned"},{"time":123058,"text":"starting in the year 2041."},{"time":129527,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":132299,"text":"people already far up north\nfrom here in the Arctic"},{"time":138267,"text":"are already taking advantage"},{"time":141378,"text":"of this ice melt,"},{"time":145325,"text":"taking out resources from areas\nalready that have been covered in ice"},{"time":151553,"text":"for the last 10, 20, 30,000,"},{"time":154961,"text":"100,000 years."},{"time":158305,"text":"Can they not join the dots"},{"time":161578,"text":"and think, \"Why is the ice\nactually melting?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":167940,"text":"This is such an amazing place,"},{"time":171284,"text":"the Antarctic, and I have worked hard"},{"time":175138,"text":"for the last 23 years on this mission"},{"time":180293,"text":"to make sure that what's happening\nup here in the North"},{"time":184297,"text":"does never happen, \ncannot happen in the South."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189716,"text":"Where did this all begin?"},{"time":191508,"text":"It began for me at the age of 11."},{"time":194457,"text":"Check out that haircut. \nIt's a bit odd. (Laughter)"},{"time":197452,"text":"And at the age of 11, \nI was inspired by the real explorers"},{"time":202556,"text":"to want to try to be the first\nto walk to both Poles."},{"time":207320,"text":"I found it incredibly inspiring"},{"time":211685,"text":"that the idea of becoming a polar traveler"},{"time":215563,"text":"went down pretty well with girls \nat parties when I was at university."},{"time":219910,"text":"That was a bit more inspiring."},{"time":221878,"text":"And after years, seven\nyears of fundraising,"},{"time":225500,"text":"seven years of being told no,"},{"time":228147,"text":"seven years of being told\nby my family to seek counseling"},{"time":234393,"text":"and psychiatric help,"},{"time":238155,"text":"eventually three of us found ourselves\nmarching to the South Geographic Pole"},{"time":244112,"text":"on the longest unassisted march\never made anywhere on Earth in history."},{"time":250140,"text":"In this photograph,\nwe are standing in an area"},{"time":253874,"text":"the size of the United States of America,"},{"time":257612,"text":"and we're on our own."},{"time":258936,"text":"We have no radio \ncommunications, no backup."},{"time":262467,"text":"Beneath our feet,\n90 percent of all the world's ice,"},{"time":270220,"text":"70 percent of all the world's fresh water."},{"time":274353,"text":"We're standing on it."},{"time":276095,"text":"This is the power of Antarctica."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280762,"text":"On this journey, we faced\nthe danger of crevasses,"},{"time":284268,"text":"intense cold,"},{"time":286566,"text":"so cold that sweat turns\nto ice inside your clothing,"},{"time":292046,"text":"your teeth can crack,"},{"time":293834,"text":"water can freeze in your eyes."},{"time":295993,"text":"Let's just say it's a bit chilly.\n(Laughter)"},{"time":299058,"text":"And after 70 desperate days,\nwe arrive at the South Pole."},{"time":303229,"text":"We had done it."},{"time":304977,"text":"But something happened to me\non that 70-day journey in 1986"},{"time":310696,"text":"that brought me here, and it hurt."},{"time":313500,"text":"My eyes changed color\nin 70 days through damage."},{"time":318615,"text":"Our faces blistered out."},{"time":320652,"text":"The skin ripped off\nand we wondered why."},{"time":325644,"text":"And when we got home,\nwe were told by NASA"},{"time":329173,"text":"that a hole in the ozone\nhad been discovered"},{"time":332029,"text":"above the South Pole,"},{"time":333562,"text":"and we'd walked underneath it\nthe same year it had been discovered."},{"time":338925,"text":"Ultraviolet rays down, hit the ice,\nbounced back, fried out the eyes,"},{"time":344896,"text":"ripped off our faces."},{"time":348027,"text":"It was a bit of a shock --\n(Laughter) --"},{"time":351371,"text":"and it started me thinking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354877,"text":"In 1989, we now head north."},{"time":358104,"text":"Sixty days, every step away\nfrom the safety of land"},{"time":362743,"text":"across a frozen ocean."},{"time":364629,"text":"It was desperately cold again."},{"time":366854,"text":"Here's me coming in from washing\nnaked at -60 Celsius."},{"time":373823,"text":"And if anybody ever says to you,\n\"I am cold\" -- (Laughter) --"},{"time":378305,"text":"if they look like this, \nthey are cold, definitely."},{"time":384040,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":386958,"text":"And 1,000 kilometers away\nfrom the safety of land,"},{"time":392982,"text":"disaster strikes."},{"time":395646,"text":"The Arctic Ocean melts beneath our feet\nfour months before it ever had in history,"},{"time":403401,"text":"and we're 1,000 kilometers from safety."},{"time":406910,"text":"The ice is crashing around us, grinding,\nand I'm thinking, \"Are we going to die?\""},{"time":413411,"text":"But something clicked\nin my head on this day,"},{"time":417614,"text":"as I realized we, as a world,\nare in a survival situation,"},{"time":424706,"text":"and that feeling has never gone away\nfor 25 long years."},{"time":429070,"text":"Back then, we had to march or die."},{"time":433543,"text":"And we're not some TV survivor program."},{"time":437351,"text":"When things go wrong for us,\nit's life or death,"},{"time":440282,"text":"and our brave African-American Daryl,"},{"time":443596,"text":"who would become the first American\nto walk to the North Pole,"},{"time":447474,"text":"his heel dropped off \nfrom frostbite 200 klicks out."},{"time":452071,"text":"He must keep going, he does,"},{"time":454231,"text":"and after 60 days on the ice,\nwe stood at the North Pole."},{"time":459061,"text":"We had done it."},{"time":460555,"text":"Yes, I became the first person in history\nstupid enough to walk to both Poles,"},{"time":465825,"text":"but it was our success."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469387,"text":"And sadly, on return home,"},{"time":473247,"text":"it was not all fun."},{"time":476382,"text":"I became very low."},{"time":478123,"text":"To succeed at something is often harder\nthan actually making it happen."},{"time":484412,"text":"I was empty, lonely,\nfinancially destroyed."},{"time":488525,"text":"I was without hope,"},{"time":490870,"text":"but hope came in the form\nof the great Jacques Cousteau,"},{"time":494585,"text":"and he inspired me to take on \nthe 2041 mission."},{"time":499981,"text":"Being Jacques, he gave me\nclear instructions:"},{"time":503153,"text":"Engage the world leaders,\ntalk to industry and business,"},{"time":507550,"text":"and above all, Rob, inspire young people,"},{"time":511489,"text":"because they will choose the future\nof the preservation of Antarctica."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516344,"text":"For the world leaders, we've been\nto every world Earth Summit,"},{"time":520730,"text":"all three of them,\nwith our brave yacht, 2041,"},{"time":525095,"text":"twice to Rio, once in '92, once in 2012,"},{"time":529925,"text":"and for the Earth Summit in Johannesburg,"},{"time":533547,"text":"we made the longest overland voyage\never made with a yacht,"},{"time":540861,"text":"13,000 kilometers around\nthe whole of Southern Africa"},{"time":545040,"text":"doing our best to inspire\nover a million young people in person"},{"time":551518,"text":"about 2041 and about their environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":556580,"text":"For the last 11 years,\nwe have taken over 1,000 people,"},{"time":563499,"text":"people from industry and business,\nwomen and men from companies,"},{"time":566518,"text":"students from all over the world,\ndown to Antarctica,"},{"time":570893,"text":"and during those missions,\nwe've managed to pull out"},{"time":574002,"text":"over 1,500 tons of twisted metal\nleft in Antarctica."},{"time":579652,"text":"That took eight years,\nand I'm so proud of it"},{"time":583111,"text":"because we recycled all of it \nback here in South America."},{"time":590246,"text":"I have been inspired\never since I could walk"},{"time":593754,"text":"to recycle by my mum."},{"time":597051,"text":"Here she is, and my mum --"},{"time":599528,"text":"(Applause) --"},{"time":603175,"text":"my mum is still recycling,"},{"time":605872,"text":"and as she is in her 100th year,\nisn't that fantastic?"},{"time":610847,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":613197,"text":"And when -- I love my mum."},{"time":616439,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":617559,"text":"But when Mum was born,"},{"time":620780,"text":"the population of our planet\nwas only 1.8 billion people,"},{"time":627119,"text":"and talking in terms of billions,"},{"time":629070,"text":"we have taken young people\nfrom industry and business"},{"time":632738,"text":"from India, from China."},{"time":634944,"text":"These are game-changing nations,\nand will be hugely important"},{"time":640724,"text":"in the decision about\nthe preservation of the Antarctic."},{"time":645544,"text":"Unbelievably, we've engaged and inspired\nwomen to come from the Middle East,"},{"time":652393,"text":"often for the first time they've \nrepresented their nations in Antarctica."},{"time":658551,"text":"Fantastic people, so inspired."},{"time":661066,"text":"To look after Antarctica,"},{"time":664322,"text":"you've got to first engage people\nwith this extraordinary place,"},{"time":670658,"text":"form a relationship, form a bond,"},{"time":674858,"text":"form some love."},{"time":677621,"text":"It is such a privilege\nto go to Antarctica,"},{"time":681080,"text":"I can't tell you."},{"time":682427,"text":"I feel so lucky,"},{"time":684006,"text":"and I've been 35 times in my life,"},{"time":687233,"text":"and all those people who come with us\nreturn home as great champions,"},{"time":691951,"text":"not only for Antarctica,"},{"time":693899,"text":"but for local issues\nback in their own nations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697543,"text":"Let's go back to where we began:\nthe ice melt of the North and South Poles."},{"time":703891,"text":"And it's not good news."},{"time":707713,"text":"NASA informed us six months ago"},{"time":711689,"text":"that the Western Antarctic Ice Shelf\nis now disintegrating."},{"time":716688,"text":"Huge areas of ice --"},{"time":719113,"text":"look how big Antarctica is\neven compared to here --"},{"time":723385,"text":"Huge areas of ice \nare breaking off from Antarctica,"},{"time":727926,"text":"the size of small nations."},{"time":730761,"text":"And NASA have calculated\nthat the sea level will rise,"},{"time":735166,"text":"it is definite,"},{"time":737340,"text":"by one meter in the next 100 years,"},{"time":740753,"text":"the same time that my mum\nhas been on planet Earth."},{"time":744288,"text":"It's going to happen,"},{"time":745978,"text":"and I've realized that \nthe preservation of Antarctica"},{"time":751649,"text":"and our survival here on Earth are linked."},{"time":756194,"text":"And there is a very simple solution."},{"time":758088,"text":"If we are using more renewable energy\nin the real world,"},{"time":763607,"text":"if we are being more efficient\nwith the energy here,"},{"time":769469,"text":"running our energy mix in a cleaner way,"},{"time":773765,"text":"there will be no financial reason\nto go and exploit Antarctica."},{"time":778611,"text":"It won't make financial sense,"},{"time":780670,"text":"and if we manage our energy better,\nwe also may be able to slow down,"},{"time":788366,"text":"maybe even stop,"},{"time":790506,"text":"this great ice melt that threatens us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793547,"text":"It's a big challenge, and what\nis our response to it?"},{"time":797097,"text":"We've got to go back one last time,"},{"time":801069,"text":"and at the end of next year,"},{"time":802965,"text":"we will go back to the\nSouth Geographic Pole,"},{"time":806800,"text":"where we arrived 30 years ago on foot,"},{"time":811052,"text":"and retrace our steps of 1,600 kilometers,"},{"time":816777,"text":"but this time only using\nrenewable energy to survive."},{"time":822827,"text":"We will walk across those icecaps,\nwhich far down below are melting,"},{"time":828386,"text":"hopefully inspiring some\nsolutions on that issue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":833295,"text":"This is my son, Barney."},{"time":835720,"text":"He is coming with me."},{"time":838511,"text":"He is committed to walking\nside by side with his father,"},{"time":843261,"text":"and what he will do is\nto translate these messages"},{"time":847275,"text":"and inspire these messages\nto the minds of future young leaders."},{"time":852900,"text":"I'm extremely proud of him."},{"time":854939,"text":"Good on him, Barney."}]},{"cues":[{"time":859623,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen, \na survivor -- and I'm good --"},{"time":866198,"text":"a survivor sees a problem\nand doesn't go, \"Whatever.\""},{"time":874686,"text":"A survivor sees a problem\nand deals with that problem"},{"time":878846,"text":"before it becomes a threat."},{"time":881919,"text":"We have 27 years\nto preserve the Antarctic."},{"time":887967,"text":"We all own it."},{"time":890482,"text":"We all have responsibility."},{"time":893262,"text":"The fact that nobody owns it \nmaybe means that we can succeed."},{"time":898232,"text":"Antarctica is a moral line in the snow,"},{"time":903051,"text":"and on one side of that line\nwe should fight,"},{"time":906598,"text":"fight hard for this one beautiful,\npristine place left alone on Earth."},{"time":912311,"text":"I know it's possible."},{"time":914472,"text":"We are going to do it."},{"time":916492,"text":"And I'll leave you with\nthese words from Goethe."},{"time":920370,"text":"I've tried to live by them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":923977,"text":"\"If you can do, or dream you can,"},{"time":931262,"text":"begin it now,"},{"time":934234,"text":"for boldness has genius,\npower and magic in it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":941026,"text":"Good luck to you all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":942590,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":944750,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}